update

protected void update(ParameterCache_mxJPO _paramCache,
                      CharSequence _preMQLCode,
                      CharSequence _postMQLCode,
                      CharSequence _preTCLCode,
                      Map<String,String> _tclVariables,
                      File _sourceFile)
               throws Exception
The method overwrites the original method to append the MQL statements in the _preMQLCode to reset this role. Following steps are done:
  • reset description
  • remove all parent groups
  • define as "normal" role

Overrides:
update in class AbstractUser_mxJPO
Parameters:
_paramCache - parameter cache
_preMQLCode - MQL statements which must be called before the TCL code is executed
_postMQLCode - MQL statements which must be called after the TCL code is executed
_preTCLCode - TCL code which is defined before the source file is sourced
_tclVariables - map of all TCL variables where the key is the name and the value is value of the TCL variable (the value is automatically converted to TCL syntax!)
_sourceFile - souce file with the TCL code to update
Throws:
Exception - if the update from derived class failed
See Also:
AbstractUser_mxJPO.ignoreWorkspaceObjects(ParameterCache_mxJPO)

ignoreWorkspaceObjects

protected boolean ignoreWorkspaceObjects(ParameterCache_mxJPO _paramCache)

Calculates if workspace objects for this role are not handled. This is done by checking if the name of this role matches one of the match lists defined with parameter PARAM_IGNORE_WSO_ROLES. In this case the the workspace objects are ignored for this role.

Overrides:
ignoreWorkspaceObjects in class AbstractUser_mxJPO
Parameters:
_paramCache - parameter cache
Returns:
true if the handling of workspace objects for this role is ignored
See Also:
PARAM_IGNORE_WSO_ROLES
